Package: morisawa-fontfiles
Version: 1.0
Revision: 4
Depends: ptex-base (>=3.1.3)
Suggests: dvipdfmx, okumura-clsfiles, xdvik
Source: ftp://ftp.ring.gr.jp/pub/text/TeX/ascii-ptex/jvf/morisawa.tar.gz
Source-MD5: 10a3a0bb382d9edf834177d0c03101f5
CompileScript: echo "Nothing to do..."
InstallScript: <<
  install -m 755 -d          %i/etc/texmf.local/fonts/tfm/ptex
  install -m 644 tfm/dvips/* %i/etc/texmf.local/fonts/tfm/ptex/
  install -m 644 tfm/ptex/*  %i/etc/texmf.local/fonts/tfm/ptex/
  install -m 755 -d          %i/etc/texmf.local/fonts/vf/ptex
  install -m 644 vf/*        %i/etc/texmf.local/fonts/vf/ptex/
  install -m 755 -d           %i/etc/texmf.local/dvips/config
  install -m 644 morisawa.map %i/etc/texmf.local/dvips/config/
<<
Docfiles: README.txt COPYRIGHT COPYRIGHT.jis
PostInstScript: <<
  echo "p +morisawa.map" >> %p/share/texmf/dvips/config/config.ps
  mktexlsr
<<
PreRmScript: <<
  sed -e "/p +morisawa.map/d" %p/share/texmf/dvips/config/config.ps > /var/run/%n.tmp.$$
  install -m 644 /var/run/%n.tmp.$$ %p/share/texmf/dvips/config/config.ps
  rm /var/run/%n.tmp.$$
<<
PostRmScript: mktexlsr
Description: TFM & VF files for morisawa fontfamily
DescDetail:<<
This package will be installed to %p/etc/texmf.local
<<
